## Build Automation Workflow

### 1. Pre-Build Validation
- Verify [Content-Website.txt](mdc:Content-Website.txt) exists and is readable
- Validate data file format (key = value pairs)
- Check for required tokens in data file

### 2. Template Processing
- Process each HTML template file
- Replace all tokens with corresponding data values
- Validate that critical tokens are replaced
- Generate warnings for missing optional tokens

### 3. Post-Build Validation
- Verify all HTML files are valid
- Check that SEO meta tags are properly populated
- Validate that all images have alt text
- Ensure all links are properly formatted

### 4. Output Generation
- Generate processed HTML files
- Create build report with token replacement statistics
- Log any warnings or errors


## Quality Assurance

### Token Coverage Validation
- Ensure all tokens in HTML templates have corresponding data
- Generate report of unused data entries
- Validate token naming consistency

### Content Validation
- Check for proper HTML structure after token replacement
- Validate SEO meta tags completeness
- Ensure accessibility attributes are present

### Performance Optimization
- Minimize HTML output
- Optimize image references
- Validate CSS and JavaScript references

This automation system ensures consistent, error-free content management while maintaining the separation between content data and HTML templates.
